  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "There is one great big and glori-\nGUS howl going up from the prop\nerty owners along Thirty-seventh\navenue between Crestline and\nPerry streets, over the improve\nment work soon to be done on that\navenue. The assessment rolls show\nthat the taxes assessed against\nproperty along this bit of proposed\nimprovement will amount to more\nthan twice the assessed value of\nthe property benefited. In spite OF\nthis fact, however, the board of\npublic works has sent a recommen-\ndation to the city council that the\nwork be proceeded with."
    }
